results.name: Numbers k such that (7^k - 5^k)/2 is prime.
comment: No other terms less than 10^5. - _Robert Price_, May 28 2012
mathematica: k=7; Do[p=Prime[n]; f=(k^p-5^p)/(k-5); If[ PrimeQ[f], Print[p] ], {n,1,100}]
